# Auto Push

After any modification to this repository (`wangyePHD.github.io`):

1. Commit with a concise message describing the change.
2. Push to `origin master` immediately — do not wait for the user to ask.

Use SSH remote (already configured):

```bash
unset GIT_ASKPASS && unset SSH_ASKPASS
GIT_SSH_COMMAND="ssh -o IdentitiesOnly=yes -i ~/.ssh/id_ed25519_wangyePHD" git push origin master
```

Only skip push if the user explicitly says not to push, or if push fails due to auth (then report the error).
